<TITLE> Heroin peddlers nabbed near airport </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Gazipur, May 10 (bdnews24.com)--A RAB team, disguised as drug traders, arrested two heroin wholesalers with one kilogram of the narcotic in their possession from the Shahjalal International Airport on Monday. Zahirul Islam, assistant director of RAB-1 in Gazipur, said they arrested Mohammed Altaf Hossain, 35, and Mohammed Kanchan Munshi, 45, from the footpath adjacent to the Monolova Hotel near the airport. They conducted the drive on a tip-off that the heroin peddlers had been running the illegal trade in surrounding areas of the airport and its adjacent railway station. The arrestees were handed over to the Airport Police Station, whose chief said a case was filed and they were being questioned. bdnew
